.TH "__add_badblock_range" 9 "__add_badblock_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__add_badblock_range \- Convert a physical address range to bad sectors
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __add_badblock_range
.BI "(struct badblocks *bb "  ","
.BI "u64 ns_offset "  ","
.BI "u64 len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bb" 12
badblocks instance to populate
.IP "ns_offset" 12
namespace offset where the error range begins (in bytes)
.IP "len" 12
number of bytes of badrange to be added
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This assumes that the range provided with (ns_offset, len) is within
the bounds of physical addresses for this namespace, i.e. lies in the
interval [ns_start, ns_start + ns_size)
